description:
Wargame for two players, originally included with issues no. 728, 729 (the regular 6-sided die) and 730 of Italian magazine "Panorama", in spring 1980.

From the rules' sheet:

"Il Golpe, a bespoke creation for "Panorama", is a war game based on a hypothetical military coup in Italy.
The game's flow simulates the typical putsch's mechanics: mutiny of military units, assaults against TV broadcasting stations, airports, nuclear plants and naval bases, riots in the streets.
The game represents a single day of war, consisting in 8 phases of 3 hours each. At the beginning of the game the "rebel" player secretly compiles a list with the opponent's  units that will mutiny, then the "government" player places his army and only after this stage is the list revealed.  At the end of the game the total value of the "strategic goals" achieved by the "rebel" player is calculated, and if his total score is higher than the "government" player's one (the sum of the objectives still under his control) the coup d'etat is successful."

Contents: 
Map of Italy (84 x 39,5 cm) with reference charts embedded;
107 cardboards chits;
1 dice;

Multiplication Monsters Of The Deep is an educational game, one in a series of four, that is designed to help children learn multiplication.

from the publisher:

Try this fast-paced card game alternative to flashcards! Players practice multiplication facts for numbers 2 through 9. Colorful illustrations add a self-checking aspect. Great for classroom activity centers or home use. Game includes 128 laminated playing cards, interesting animal facts and multilingual instruction book. For 2&ndash;4 players, grades 2&ndash;5.

from Spielbox:

A new Bremen-based publisher without a website as of yet. They will be releasing a game that apparently has been making the rounds of insiders for the past 10 years. The title: Paaren / Couples. It's a card-playing game. Each player plays cards. In one spot, one man can be matched with a suitable woman. Matches are determined by having at least two matching characteristics with both the location and the partner. These can be different, though. Players always have four characteristics, locations have two to six. There are influence cards which can break up matches as well as destroy them. Thankfully there are also other cards which offer protection against jealousy. The first player to reach a pre-set number of matches wins the game.

The game will be bilingual (German / English) and come with 120 individually illustrated cards. Since most will recognize the characters, it will be great fun to match those who might not seem to be such a good match to start.

