Whooops is a retro dexterity challenge from 1968 that combines physical balance, spatial planning, and a whole lot of laughter. Players take turns stepping from one plastic cup to another, trying to collect numbered cups in order&mdash;without touching the ground. It&rsquo;s a full-body balancing act where one wrong move results in the game&rsquo;s namesake: &ldquo;Whooops!&rdquo;

Players earn points by successfully retrieving as many cups as they can in sequence, while carefully maintaining balance. Once a cup is lifted, it can&rsquo;t be set down again, and touching the floor with any part of your body&mdash;including shoes&mdash;ends your turn. First player to reach 25 points wins.

Originally dubbed &ldquo;a new generation game,&rdquo; Whooops encouraged physical play indoors or outdoors and is a fascinating (and slightly perilous) throwback to a pre-safety-conscious era of gaming.
